So that if you calculate the
proportion of the U.S.

00:14:48.350 --> 00:14:51.379
population that lives in
coastal counties,

00:14:51.379 --> 00:14:54.408
it's now over fifty percent of
the U.S.

00:14:54.408 --> 00:14:57.090
population that lives in these
shaded areas.

00:14:57.090 --> 00:15:01.798
And the areas of most rapid
growth include the northeastern

00:15:01.798 --> 00:15:05.207
part of the U.S.,
particularly southern New

00:15:05.207 --> 00:15:07.399
Hampshire and Cape Cod.
 

00:15:07.399 --> 00:15:10.629
Also, Long Island,
but parts of Maryland.

